result.name: The Butchers Club

reviews.text: Amazing burger joint. We had been traveling for a few months and we finally found a burger that is worth having. The spicy chicken sandwich was also really good. The restaurant is pretty small so if you go at peak times you may have to wait a bit but it’s worth it. They do take credit cards and serve booze. If you are looking for a burger in Hong Kong then you should give this place a try.

I've been a regular here and used to come here every week at least twice for my favourite Beyond Classic. There usually is a charming and helpful Indonesian lady, who wan't there today. I ordered my usual burger. When I asked one of the staff for a regular fork and steak knife, he told me that they'd done away with regular cutlery and that wooden disposable ones were the only options!
Not only is this unfriendly to the environment, I would never pay what they charge for eating with disposable cutlery!

Great burger and fries. Meat was tender and juicy, probably the best burger patty I've had. Duck fat fries were on point. Everything was fresh. Only wish they were a bit more generous with the fresh veggies topping like in the photos.
The best hamburger I have ever ate. I highly recommend it. I tried the double happiness burger, which is too big, but for sure, it brings happiness.

A proper burger place, full fatty and pure joy. Not the fast food sort with unrecognizable meats and cheap bread, they serve a grilled slice with a good bun and an assortment of customizable toppings. Personally love the classic and the hogtown burgers. The sides are secondary but also equally yummy, the duck fat fries and a draft beer are perfect to complete this burger meal.
